The paper deals with channel pruning in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and proposes a new perspective on channel pruning based on redundancy reduction. The paper also involves empirical studies and statistical modeling (cs.AI) to validate their hypothesis. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks (cs.CL) as they use language related to neural networks and pruning. Finally, the paper involves neural networks (cs.NE) as they are the subject of the study.
